HEADWORD: Fibrovascular
<hw>Fi`bro*vas"cu*lar</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>fibra</ets> a fiber + E. <ets>vascular</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>Containing woody fiber and ducts, as the stems of
all flowering plants and ferns; -- opposed to
<xex>cellular</xex>.</def>⟦br⟧
